The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence during a visit to the USC School of Medicine in Greenville, South Carolina. Pence thanked Governor Henry McMaster and other state leaders for their leadership during the COVID-19 pandemic. He also expressed gratitude to congressmen Jeff Duncan and William Timmons for their support in providing resources to South Carolina. Pence highlighted the progress made in testing, the development of therapeutics and vaccines, and the upcoming approval of the first coronavirus vaccine. He emphasized that the administration is working to ensure the vaccine is distributed and administered quickly. Pence urged the people of South Carolina to continue following health guidelines to slow the spread of the virus. He expressed confidence that the nation will get through the pandemic with the help of healthcare workers, scientific innovation, government cooperation, and the American people.